<br>
I do appreciate when groups have let me loot the sellables but I am more appreciative of good xp so doesnt really matter . <br>
<br>
Honestly I can really only think of 2 camps where that matters and thats Guardian and Gang in Seb . In my experience those are the 2 spots with mad gem/sellable drop rates .They are also the only spots where I have made any pp above the cost of the peridot I used . So it evens out the other spots where I havent even began to cover my cost in Peridot .  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utuffongrease.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuffon Grease</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#778899>(1/3/02 10:57:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric rant =)</span><hr size=1> As my Wizard, I don't care if I get symbol or not.. I have my Epic, and I have concussion, so can keep agro off myself.. but I let the clerics loot the gems or whatever if they want.  To me it's not that big of a deal, if the cleirc makes a fortune, so be it.<br>
<br>
As my Warrior, if I have say, the cleics get sellables (most of the time they are willing to split them with the other members in the group who need some cash).  When I'm playing my warrior, I basically demand Symbol.. I am usually the main tank in a group, but even when I'm not.. if the cleric has to heal me with Cheal.. it saves them a lot of mana with the extra 400+ hp's that I get from a Symbol....  <p><B>Tuffon Grease</B><br>
<i>Halfling Steam-Roller of Norrath</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ulorileibard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LorileiBard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#778899>(1/3/02 10:59:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric rant =)</span><hr size=1> I'm all totally fine with sellables, non-quest gems, what-have-you going to the cleric for symbols peridots.  I have no problem with a cleric asking for an extra quest gem or two in SG or Velks if you are on mobs who don't drop decent sellables.<br>
<br>
So far as cash goes, it should be split.  I pay for ports all the time, and pay for res's, too (either in pp or in peridots).<br>
<br>
That being said...I've been with a cleric recently who has been ML'ing, but has forgotten to do the split for the cash at the end several times, has walked with the smaller loot with no /ran (quest gems and items worth less than 5k, but more than 1k), and has asked for str buffs from being encumbered from the loot/coins.  After the third time grouping, and this about to happen again, I pushed for the split and the /ran for the loot.<br>
<br>
It's not going to happen a 4th time.  *IF* I group with that cleric again, I'm going to ask for a different person to be the ML.  <br>
<br>
BTW, same cleric has needed med breaks.  Sorry, but if you need med breaks, you should be sitting on your a$$ medding, not looting the stuff that you won't be splitting with the group at the end.<br>
